data.name: Sous Vide Beef Wellington with Herb Infused Mashed Potatoes
data.quickTastyDescription: A luxurious and tender beef Wellington, perfectly cooked sous vide, enveloped in a flaky pastry with a side of creamy, herb-infused mashed potatoes.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat the sous vide water bath to 130°F (54°C) for medium-rare.
Season the beef tenderloin with salt and black pepper. Sear on all sides in a hot pan for 2-3 minutes until browned.
Vacuum seal the beef and cook in the sous vide bath for 2-3 hours.
In a food processor, blend the chopped mushrooms until finely minced. Sauté with garlic in butter until all moisture is evaporated. Season to taste and allow to cool.

Lay out prosciutto slices on a sheet of plastic wrap, overlapping them slightly. Spread the cooled mushroom mixture over the prosciutto, then place the beef in the center and roll tightly, forming a log. Chill for 30 minutes.
Roll out puff pastry and wrap around the beef log. Brush with egg yolk and seal edges.
Bake at 400°F (200°C) for 25-30 minutes until pastry is golden brown. Let rest for 10 minutes before slicing.
For the mashed potatoes, boil peeled potatoes until tender. Drain and mash with heavy cream, butter, thyme, salt, and pepper until smooth.
